# Keep the Docker build context small (review M-17): the image only needs pyproject +
# packages + services, but the build context is the repo root, so without this the web UI's
# node_modules, the .git history, the local venv, and caches were shipped to the daemon for
# every one of the 8 service images.
.git
.gitignore
.venv
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
.pytest_cache
.mypy_cache
.ruff_cache

# UI is built separately, not baked into the Python service image.
web/node_modules
web/.next
node_modules

# Docs, eval corpora, and scratch aren't needed at runtime.
docs
eval
tests
scratchpad
*.md
!README.md
